SLS 26RS-4589 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 187
BY SENATOR CARTER
LAW ENFORCEMENT. Requests the LCLE to report to the Senate Committee on Judiciary
B on the progress of the implementation of Act 426 of the 2025 Regular Session.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request the Louisiana Commission on Law Enforcement and the Administration
3 of Criminal Justice (LCLE) to report to the Senate Committee on Judiciary B on the
4 progress of the implementation of Act 426 of the 2025 Regular Session.
5 WHEREAS, the Louisiana Commission on Law Enforcement and the Administration
6 of Criminal Justice is charged with supporting, coordinating, and enhancing the effectiveness
7 of the state's criminal justice system; and
8 WHEREAS, Act 426 of the 2025 Regular Session established important requirements
9 that the P.O.S.T. Council adopt a policy regarding mandatory reporting when a peace officer
10 uses force, under certain circumstances; and
11 WHEREAS, the successful implementation of Act 426 is essential to achieving the
12 Legislature's goals of improving public safety, enhancing accountability, and ensuring
13 consistent standards across law enforcement agencies; and
14 WHEREAS, ongoing legislative oversight is necessary to monitor progress, identify
15 challenges, and ensure that the provisions of Act 426 are being carried out as intended; and
16 WHEREAS, the Senate Committee on Judiciary B is the appropriate body to receive
17 updates and evaluate the status of implementation efforts.
18 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
